  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Synergies of ESD and GCE in Pacific Education</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Education for Sustainable Development (including CCE) and Global Citizenship Education have increasing but diverse profiles within the Education Systems of the Pacific. Countries have identified that there is significant need to address these two areas within the context of SDG 4.7 building identity and resilience (physical, social and emotional) in young people as well as the empathy, respect for people and the environment and intercultural competencies to be balanced, contributing young people in the 21st century. This workplan will assist countries to identify where ESD and GCE sit in current curricula and support the development of relevant contextualized resources and teaching strategies to strengthen opportunities for young learners to engage with the intended outcomes of SDG 4.7</narrative>
  </description>
